. Drizzle oil in a 3-quart soup pot and swirl it around until the oil coats the entire surface of the bottom of the pan. Heat over high heat for 1 minute. Add cumin and coriander. Cook and stir until fragrant, about 30 seconds. Add the celery, carrot, onion, leek, and garlic. Cook and stir until onion and leek are tender, about 5 minutes. Add the Basic Vegetable Stock, water, lentils, and Bouquet Garni. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to simmering and cook for 45 to 60 minutes, stirring occasionally. Stir in lemon juice, salt, and lemon zest. Remove Bouquet Garni. Season to taste with pepper.